    <h2>White Wine</h2>
    <p>Certain flavours round each other out to perfection. The successful food and wine pairer will consider the dominant flavour of the dish they are serving the white wine with. Light wines with good acidity, for instance, bring out the best in shellfish, shrimp and lean fish, while rounder, fat-textured, more intense wines harmonize with dishes in cream sauce, or baked Brie. Dishes seasoned with fruit, lemongrass or ginger, or slightly sweet dishes, will be enhanced with a wine with residual sugar.</p>
