    <h2>Rosé</h2>
    <p>When they’re light and fruity, rosés are the ideal aperitif. They’re also good with fish or shellfish, salads, or pastas with a light, fresh sauce. More generous, affirmative rosés go splendidly with more substantial dishes like salmon, veal or pork. Sweet, fruity wines, delicious as aperitifs, go well with white meats, poultry and fish with sweet-and-sour or fruit sauces.</p>
